<subSubSection box="[189,1327,266,293]" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,158,797]" box="[189,1327,266,293]" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,318,266,292]" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">Etymology</emphasis>
:—The varietal epithet refers to the long spines present in the lateral margins of semicells.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="236" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,158,797]" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,447,302,328]" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
:—Morphologically, the newly described 
<taxonomicName box="[927,1127,302,328]" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" rank="variety" variety="resembles">variety resembles</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authority="West (1892: 167" authorityName="West" authorityYear="1892" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Xanthidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" phylum="Charophyta" rank="variety" species="concinnum" variety="boldtianum">
<emphasis box="[1137,1400,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">Xanthidium concinnum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[136,264,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">boldtianum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="West, W." box="[274,468,338,365]" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" pagination="713 - 48" refId="ref9725" refString="West, W. (1892) Algae of the English Lake District. Journal of the Royal Microscopy Society 1892: 713 - 48. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2818.1892. tb 05529. x" type="journal article" year="1892">West (1892: 167</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, as ‘ 
<emphasis box="[528,635,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">boldtiana</emphasis>
’) and 
<taxonomicName authority="C. E. M. Bicudo" authorityName="C. E. M. Bicudo" box="[716,1286,338,365]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Xanthidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" phylum="Charophyta" rank="variety" species="concinnum" variety="scottii">
<emphasis box="[716,981,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">Xanthidium concinnum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1044,1112,339,364]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">scottii</emphasis>
C.E.M.Bicudo
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Prescott, G. W. &amp; Bicudo, C. E. M. &amp; Vinyard, W. C." pageId="8" pageNumber="236" refId="ref8840" refString="Prescott, G. W., Bicudo, C. E. M. &amp; Vinyard, W. C. (1982) A Synopsis of North American Desmids. Part II. Desmidiaceae: Placodermae. Section 4. University of Nebraska Press, Lincoln, 700 pp." type="book" year="1982">
Prescott 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">et al.</emphasis>
(1982: 62)
</bibRefCitation>
. However, the former differs by having no short apical spines on each apical angle and central obtuse protrusion on the face of semicells, whereas the latter differs by having downward-projected spines at the lateral margins and the mid-region of the semicells.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="236" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,158,797]" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">
<treatmentCitationGroup pageId="8" pageNumber="236">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos &amp; Ramos &amp; Moura" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,646,482,509]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Xanthidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" phylum="Charophyta" rank="variety" species="concinnum" variety="longispinum">
<emphasis box="[189,451,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">Xanthidium concinnum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[508,646,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">longispinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be compared to 
<treatmentCitation author="Therezien, Y." page=")" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" year="1985">
<taxonomicName authority="Therezien (1985: 121)" authorityName="Therezien" authorityPageNumber="121" authorityYear="1985" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Xanthidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="8" pageNumber="236" phylum="Charophyta" rank="variety" species="concinnum" variety="guyanense">
<emphasis box="[920,1075,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">X. concinnum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1132,1250,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">guyanense</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Therezien, Y." pageId="8" pageNumber="236" pagination="5 - 275" refId="ref9668" refString="Therezien, Y. (1985) Contribution a l'etude des algues d'eau douce de la Guyane Francaise (a l'exclusion des Diatomees). Bibliotheca Phycologica 72: 5 - 275." type="journal article" year="1985">Thérézien (1985: 121)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
, an endemic variety from 
<collectingCountry box="[482,651,518,544]" name="French Guiana" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
, which differs mostly by lacking the crown of small spines surrounding the lateral spine.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,158,797]" pageId="8" pageNumber="236">We also observed variation in spines dimensions in the apical angles, from longer (2.5–3 μm long) to shorter (0.3–1 μm long), which is difficult to view. The spine on the lateral margin of the semicells can be slightly or widely converging, and sometimes measuring approximately 1/3 of the width of the cell.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
